clinical_study.brief_title: Study to Evaluate GSK Biologicals' Herpes Zoster Vaccine GSK1437173A in Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV)-Infected Subjects
clinical_study.official_title: Safety and Immunogenicity of GlaxoSmithKline Biologicals' Herpes Zoster Vaccine 1437173A in Adult HIV-infected Subjects

brief_summary.textblock:
This observer-blind study will evaluate the safety and immunogenicity of GlaxoSmithKline (GSK) Biologicals' investigational Herpes Zoster (HZ) vaccine GSK1437173A in Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV) infected subjects, firstly enrolling subjects treated with antiretroviral therapy (ART) and with high CD4 T cell counts, and subsequently ART-treated subjects with low CD4 T cell counts, and ART-naïve subjects with high CD4 T cell counts.
This Protocol Posting has been updated following Amendment 1 of the Protocol, August 2010. The impacted sections is exclusion criteria.

primary_outcome.measure: Number of Subjects With Serious Adverse Events (SAEs)
primary_outcome.description: Serious adverse events (SAEs) assessed include medical occurrences that result in death, are life threatening, require hospitalization or prolongation of hospitalization or result in disability/incapacity.

primary_outcome.measure: Number of Subjects With SAEs Related to Study Participation or to a Concurrent GSK Medication/Vaccine
primary_outcome.time_frame: From screening (up to 21 days prior to Month 0) until Month 18

primary_outcome.measure: Number of Subjects With Any Fatal SAEs
primary_outcome.time_frame: From screening (up to 21 days prior to Month 0) until Month 18
primary_outcome.description: Serious adverse events (SAEs) assessed include medical occurrences that result in death, are life threatening, require hospitalization or prolongation of hospitalization or result in disability/incapacity.

primary_outcome.measure: Number of Subjects With Any Adverse Events (AEs) of Specific Interest
primary_outcome.description: AEs of specific interest include new onset of autoimmune diseases (NOADs) and other immune mediated inflammatory disorders from administration of the first dose of vaccine/placebo.

primary_outcome.measure: Number of Subjects With Any, Grade 3 and Related Solicited Local Symptoms
primary_outcome.time_frame: Within the 7-day (Days 0-6) post-vaccination period following each dose and across doses
primary_outcome.description: Assessed solicited local symptoms were pain, redness and swelling. Any = incidence of a particular symptom regardless of their intensity grade. Grade 3 pain = pain that prevented normal activity. Grade 3 redness/swelling = redness/swelling spreading beyond 100 millimeters (mm) of injection site.

primary_outcome.measure: Number of Subjects With Any, Grade 3 and Related Solicited General Symptoms
primary_outcome.time_frame: Within the 7-day (Days 0-6) post-vaccination period following each dose and across doses
primary_outcome.description: Assessed solicited general symptoms were fatigue, gastrointestinal (symptoms included nausea, vomiting, diarrhoea and/or abdominal pain), headache, myalgia, shivering and temperature [defined as oral/axillary temperature above (>) 37.5 degrees Celsius (°C)]. Any = incidence of a particular symptom regardless of their intensity grade or relationship to vaccination. Grade 3 symptom = symptom that prevented normal activity. Grade 3 fever = fever > 39.0 °C. Related = symptom assessed by the investigator as related to the vaccination.

primary_outcome.measure: Number of Subjects With Unsolicited AEs
primary_outcome.description: An unsolicited AE covers any untoward medical occurrence in a clinical investigation subject temporally associated with the use of a medicinal product, whether or not considered related to the medicinal product and reported in addition to those solicited during the clinical study and any solicited symptom with onset outside the specified period of follow-up for solicited symptoms. Any was defined as the occurrence of any unsolicited AE regardless of intensity grade or relation to vaccination. Grade 3 AE = an AE which prevented normal, everyday activities. Related = AE assessed by the investigator as related to the vaccination.

primary_outcome.measure: Number of Subjects With Any Significant Change in Antiretroviral Therapy (ART), Including Initiation of ART in ART-naïve Subjects
primary_outcome.description: In this analysis, results were tabulated for the main study groups. Significant changes to ART appeared due to failure to control HIV viral load and due to failure to maintain high CD4 cells count.

primary_outcome.measure: Frequency of gE-specific CD4 T-cells
primary_outcome.description: The analysis focused on CD4 T-cells expressing at least 2 cytokines (among interferon-gamma (IFN-g) , interleukin-2 (IL-2), tumour necrosis factor-alpha (TNF-a) and/or CD40 ligand (CD40L)) as determined by in vitro intracellular cytokine staining (ICS) at Month 7 in ART and non-ART cohorts presenting high CD4 counts at enrollment.

primary_outcome.measure: -Anti-gE Antibody (Ab) Concentrations
primary_outcome.description: -Anti-gE antibody (Ab) concentrations were determined by Enzyme-Linked Immunosorbent Assay (ELISA) at Month 7 in ART and non-ART cohorts presenting high CD4 counts at enrolment. Antibody concentrations were presented as geometric mean concentrations (GMCs) and expressed in milli-international units per milliliter (mIU/mL).

secondary_outcome.measure: -Frequencies of Varicella-Zoster Virus (VZV)- and gE-specific CD4 T-cells
secondary_outcome.description: The analysis focused on CD4 T cells expressing at least 2 cytokines (among IFN-g, IL-2, TNF-a and/or CD40L as determined by ICS at Months 0, 1, 2, 3, 6, 7 and 18 and tabulated for the main study groups.

secondary_outcome.measure: -Frequencies of Varicella-Zoster Virus (VZV)- and gE-specific CD4 T-cells, by HIV Status
secondary_outcome.description: The analysis focused on CD4 T-cells expressing at least 2 cytokines (among IFN-g, IL-2, TNF-a and/or CD40L as determined by ICS at Months 0, 1, 2, 3, 6, 7 and 18 and tabulated by HIV status.

Antibody concentrations were as determined by ELISA and tabulated for the main study groups. Anti-VZV and anti-gE antibody concentrations were presented as geometric mean concentrations (GMCs) and expressed in mIU/mL.

secondary_outcome.measure: -Anti-VZV and Anti-gE Antibody Concentrations, by HIV Status
secondary_outcome.description: Antibody concentrations were as determined by ELISA and tabulated by HIV status. Anti-VZV and anti-gE antibody concentrations were presented as geometric mean concentrations (GMCs) and expressed in mIU/mL.

secondary_outcome.measure: Number of Subjects With Any Herpes Zoster (HZ) Cases and Complications

secondary_outcome.time_frame: At Screening Visit (up to 21 days prior to Month 0), Months 1, 2, 3, 6, 7 and 18
secondary_outcome.description: CD4 count was tabulated by HIV status.

secondary_outcome.time_frame: At Screening Visit (up to 21 days prior to Month 0), Months 1, 2, 3, 6, 7 and 18
secondary_outcome.description: HIV VL was tabulated by HIV status, for subjects with a number of available results greater than or equal to (≥) 40 copies/mL.
